<DevelopmentPlan VERSION="3.7.0">
  <ArchitectureNotes>
    <objective>Ship and maintain the GRACE methodology as a Claude Code marketplace plugin + npm-published CLI, with a self-dogfooded reference project so agents cannot forget the framework they ship.</objective>
    <non-goal>Be a generic engineering-advice framework. GRACE is domain-specific (contract-first, graph-anchored, verification-first) — the skills are not interchangeable with plain prompting rules.</non-goal>
    <risk-1>Drift between canonical `skills/grace/*` and packaged `plugins/grace/skills/grace/*`. Mitigated by scripts/validate-marketplace.ts.</risk-1>
    <risk-2>LLM forgets to activate GRACE when the repo is GRACE-managed. Mitigated by the grace-bootstrap meta-skill + SessionStart hook + CLAUDE.md preamble.</risk-2>
    <risk-3>Skill docs drift out of the three-section discipline (Common Rationalizations / When NOT to Use / Verification). Mitigated by `grace lint` skill-section warnings.</risk-3>
  </ArchitectureNotes>

